name: Diane Joyce Cook
content: Diane J. Cook Diane J. Cook Publications Teaching CASAS CV I am a Regents Professor in the School of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science at Washington State University. My research interests include AI, machine learning, behavior modeling from sensor time series, and digital health. I lead the CASAS lab and work with a talented crew who are passionate about designing human digital twins for health assessment and intervention.
